          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The HgO powder (99.5% pure, natural isotopic",
                "composition) was placed in a polymethyl methacrylate",
                "sample box. Three samples with a diameter of 20 mm",
                "and six niobium foil monitors (of 99.99% purity) with",
                "identical diameters were prepared for irradiation.",
                "The HgO samples were 0.0537 cm, 0.0538 cm, and",
                "0.0559 cm thick."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High-purity germanium (HPGe) gamma-ray",
                "spectroscopy (about 68% relative efficiency, 1.69",
                "keV resolution at 1332.5 keV of 60Co). The detector",
                "was coupled with a digital gamma spectrometry system",
                " (ORTEC, model GEM 60P) and Maestro data acquisition",
                "software. The distance from sample to detector end",
                "cap was 0 to 8 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A stack of Nb-HgO-Nb was assembled from these",
                "three samples and mounted at 0, 90, and 135 deg",
                "relative to the beam direction. The samples were",
                "wrapped in a cadmium foil in order to reduce the",
                "contribution of thermal and epithermal effects.",
                "Cooling time is 18 hours."
              ]
            }
          ],
